File: Supporters during the Absa Premiership match between Orlando Pirates and Kaizer Chiefs at FNB Stadium on October 27, 2018 in Johannesburg. JOHANNESBURG - The Carling Black Label Cup will bring roads leading to Soweto to a standstill on Saturday. Roads around FNB stadium will be closed for the Soweto Derby between Kaizer Chiefs and Orlando Pirates. The Soweto highway will be blocked off between N1 and Booysens from 10am until after the game at 5pm. READ: Undercover police to be deployed for Soweto derby Traffic will be managed on the roads around FNB Stadium on Saturday for Carling Black Label Cup. “There will be a conversion of three lanes towards the stadium on Nasrec Road before the match and three lanes away from the stadium after the match. Fans are encouraged to arrive early to avoid traffic congestion, gates will open at 11am and there will be musical entertainment for fans who arrive early,” said Johannesburg Metropolitan Police Department (JMPD) spokesperson, Wayne Minnaar. JMPD officers will be on duty on all road and around the stadium.